<section id="overview">
      <h2>Year Overview</h2>
      <p>The Snake (<span class="chinese-char">蛇</span>) occupies the Earthly Branch <strong>Si (巳)</strong>, carrying Yin Fire energy with hidden Metal and Earth. In 2026, the Snake enjoys a <strong>Si-Wu Liu He combination</strong> (巳午合) with the Horse year — a deeply harmonious pairing that signifies mutual support and shared purpose.</p>
      <p>Both Snake and Horse belong to the Fire family, and their combination creates <strong>intensified Fire energy</strong>. For the Snake, whose fire is naturally contained and strategic (Yin Fire, like a candle or forge), the Horse year's Yang Fire (like the sun) amplifies visibility and influence. The Snake's natural gift for working behind the scenes is complemented by Fire's spotlight — strategic insights gain a wider audience.</p>
      <p>This is a year of <strong>transformation</strong>. The Snake's ancient association with shedding skin resonates with 2026's energy of renewal. Old identities, outdated strategies, and stagnant situations can be released in favour of more authentic expressions. The process may be uncomfortable but leads to genuine growth.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="liu-he-bond">
      <h2>The Snake-Horse Liu He Bond (巳午六合)</h2>
      <div class="callout-box callout-box--jade">
        <div class="callout-icon">🤝</div>
        <div class="callout-content">
          <h3>Liu He — The Secret Friend</h3>
          <p>The Snake (Si/巳) and Horse (Wu/午) form a <strong>Liu He</strong> (六合) bond — one of six classical pairings that represent deep, innate compatibility. Unlike the San He triangle which creates collective strength, the Liu He is an intimate one-to-one bond: the <strong>"secret friend"</strong> who understands you without words.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>The Si-Wu pairing is unique among the six Liu He bonds because both animals share the <strong>Fire element</strong>. The Snake carries Yin Fire (丁, Ding — candlelight, refined intelligence) while the Horse carries Yang Fire (丙, Bing — the blazing sun, bold action). Together they represent fire in its full spectrum: from the subtle flame of insight to the powerful blaze of achievement.</p>
      <p>What the Liu He bond means for Snake-born people in 2026:</p>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><strong>Innate resonance</strong> — the year's energy feels natural rather than foreign; your instincts are reliable guides</li>
        <li><strong>Strategic advantage</strong> — the Snake's patience and cunning combine with the Horse's boldness; plan quietly, then act decisively</li>
        <li><strong>Excess fire warning</strong> — double fire without a balancing element can lead to burnout, inflammation, or recklessness; introduce Water or Earth activities for balance</li>
        <li><strong>Transformation power</strong> — the Snake is the zodiac's symbol of shedding and renewal; 2026's fire energy accelerates personal transformation</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Classical context:</strong> In the <em>Huainanzi</em> (淮南子, 139 BCE), the Si-Wu axis corresponds to the peak of summer — maximum yang energy. The Snake-Horse alliance harnesses this peak energy for transformation, but like summer itself, it requires shade and water to sustain.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>The Liu He combination makes 2026 one of the <strong>strongest career years</strong> for the Snake. Strategic thinking meets opportunity — the Snake's ability to read situations and plan several moves ahead is perfectly supported by Fire's energy of action. Leadership opportunities arise, particularly in roles requiring vision, transformation, or crisis management.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> benefits from the Snake's natural shrewdness amplified by Fire's boldness. Investment returns are strong, particularly in technology, energy, and transformation-oriented sectors. The Snake's hidden Metal energy (representing wealth in Fire charts) is activated, suggesting income from multiple sources.</p>
      <p><strong>Best sectors:</strong> Finance, technology, strategy consulting, research, energy, transformation industries, psychology, and investigation.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>The doubled Fire energy makes 2026 a <strong>passionate and intense romantic year</strong>. The Snake's magnetic appeal is at maximum — the combination of mystery (Yin Fire) and warmth (Yang Fire influence) is deeply attractive. Existing relationships experience renewed passion and deeper intimacy.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Snakes</strong> may find transformative romantic connections. The Liu He combination favours relationships that fundamentally change both partners for the better. Connections formed during the first half of the year have particular depth. However, the Snake must guard against possessiveness — doubled Fire can create jealousy.</p>
      <p><strong>Trust</strong> is the key theme. The Snake's natural guardedness relaxes under the Horse year's warm influence, allowing deeper vulnerability and connection.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>Doubled Fire energy creates risk of <strong>heat-related conditions</strong> — inflammation, skin issues, eye strain, and cardiovascular stress. The Snake should actively incorporate cooling practices: adequate hydration, cooling foods (cucumber, watermelon, mung bean), and avoidance of excessive spicy food and alcohol.</p>
      <p><strong>Heart and small intestine</strong> (Fire's organs in Chinese medicine) need monitoring. Regular cardiovascular exercise — moderate rather than extreme — supports heart health without further inflaming the system.</p>
      <p>The Snake benefits from <strong>Water-element activities</strong>: swimming, time near lakes or oceans, and meditation focusing on stillness and depth. These counterbalance the year's intense Fire without suppressing its beneficial energy.</p>
    </section>

